Author: MARKHAM
Vol / Page: 34
Edition:
Quote: One [creeper] is particularly useful. It is like Ivy growing up  large Trees, called Hoccar [he ake] [check whether sic by ed. or whether should be he aka] and can be easily found in the Woods... He used Gum tree from Sydney for Keels, Coudy planks, Hoc-car [aka] Timber and Kicaitore Knees, sometimes Pouriedie Keels.
Notes: 1963 ed.

